<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Control a Robot ’s</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Motion using Linear Actuators</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="preparation">Linear actuators are popularly used in robotic applications .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="span">They are designed</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="4" relname="purpose">to help the robot to perform complex motions .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1008" relname="span">While there are advanced methods</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">of using the linear actuator for robotic movements ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1009" relname="span">this is a simple method</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="8" relname="elaboration">that one can try .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="11" relname="circumstance">As linear actuators require an external power source ,</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="span">you will require a DC motor with an attached gearbox .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="joint">You will also need a servo motor controller and a micro controller .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1012" relname="joint">Other general tools include a drill , an aluminum sheet , fasteners , and four small wheels .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="preparation">Decide on the Primary Attributes .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="preparation">The first thing you need to do</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1017" relname="joint">is decide on the actuator ’s primary characteristics of movement , length , and speed .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">Depending on the size of the robot and its accessories ,</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="elaboration">determine the maximum distance of the length and movement of the linear actuator .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">Decide on the speed of the actuator and the amount of force</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="elaboration">it should place on the robotic components .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1017" relname="joint">Install the Motor .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">Choose a DC motor</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="sequence">that can run on low torque</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="sequence">and perform quick rotations at the same time .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="span">You need to use the aluminum sheet</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="26" relname="purpose">to install the motor to the robot ’s body .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1017" relname="joint">Drill two holes into the top left and bottom right hand corners of the sheet .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1029" relname="sequence">Drill two similar holes into the installation panel of the motor .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1030" relname="joint">Then install the motor onto the robot with the fasteners .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1030" relname="joint">Connect the Controllers .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1032" relname="sequence">First , connect the servo motor controller to the DC motor .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1033" relname="joint">Then connect the servo controller to the micro controller .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1033" relname="joint">This will provide the power supply to the robot and the actuator .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1037" relname="span">The micro controller will also help you to decide on the amount of power</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="elaboration">needed</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="purpose">to run the robot and the actuator .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="span">The servo motor controller is also used</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="38" relname="purpose">to ensure the correct amount of voltage for the linear actuator .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1033" relname="joint">Install the Wheels .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="span">The wheels are installed to the robot</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="purpose">to simply provide fluid movement to the robot during the application .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1033" relname="joint">Drill holes into the wheels</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1033" relname="joint">and attach them to the robot and the motor .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">Use the fasteners</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="purpose">to install the wheels properly onto the devices .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1047" relname="span">Turn on the Motor .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1050" relname="circumstance">Once the motor is turned on ,</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1050" relname="span">you adjust the amount of power</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="49" relname="elaboration">that you need for the application .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="span">Generally , linear actuator comes with control boxes and remote controls</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="51" relname="elaboration">that allow you to control the movement of the actuator .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1053" relname="joint">For small robotic applications , you should use DC linear actuators .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1055" relname="span">They consist of a screw ,</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1056" relname="span">which turns with the rotations of the motor ,</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="elaboration">thus creating the necessary actuator movement .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="59" relname="condition">If your application requires the robot to lift a heavy object ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1058" relname="span">then pneumatic or hydraulic linear actuators would be the best choices .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1059" relname="span">These actuators are designed</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1060" relname="joint">to provide long strokes</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1060" relname="joint">and move at high speeds .</segment>
